## Phase 13: Final UI Polish & Critical Bug Fixes

To ensure production-readiness, several critical user-experience and stability issues were resolved in **Phase 13**:

### 1. Authentication & Routing Stabilization
- **Audit Middleware Fix**: Restored missing `logAudit` exports in `auditMiddleware.js` which previously caused a silent backend crash during the login flow (`logAudit is not a function`).
- **Login Redirect Fix**: Fixed an issue where the `/login` route appeared to hang or blank out after successful authentication. This was resolved by fixing the downstream `<Dashboard>` component crash (detailed below), allowing `react-router-dom` to cleanly navigate the user to their dashboard.

### 2. Navbar Layout & Aesthetics
- **Proportional Spacing (`flex-1`)**: Removed the restrictive `max-w-7xl` container and implemented a `w-full px-8` layout.
- **Perfect Visual Balance**: Utilized CSS Flexbox `flex-1` distributions (`justify-start`, `justify-center`, `justify-end`) to evenly spread the Logo, Navigation Links, and User Profile Actions across wide screens (e.g., 1920px). This fully resolves the clustered "pill" appearance where the 11 navigation elements felt squashed on the left half of the screen.

### 3. Dashboard Chart Integration & Crash Prevention
- **Component Injection**: Successfully mounted the `Chart.js` visual components (`RevenueChart`, `OccupancyChart`, `PaymentStatusChart`) into the main `Dashboard.jsx` view.
- **Runtime Crash Fix**: Prevented a fatal React rendering crash caused by canvas gradient initialization (`ctx.createLinearGradient`). Added safe bounding checks (`chartArea`) and fallback solid colors to ensure charts render gracefully even when data is empty or dimensions are uninitialized.
- **Dummy Data Hydration**: Passed sample visual data arrays to the charts so the dashboard appears lively and fully populated upon first login.

### 4. PDF Reporting Implementation
- **Dashboard Export**: Hooked up the `generatePaymentReport` utility to the "Export" button in the Revenue Overview section.
- **Admin Panel Exports**: Hooked up the `generateAuditReport` and `generatePaymentReport` utilities to the Audit Log and Transaction History views respectively.
- Users and Admins can now download fully branded `jsPDF` generated reports with single-click actions.
